"RCH0001Written evidence submitted by Paul Sellars, a director of PJL Healthcare Limited, the owner of Mayfield Children’s Home, East Sussex. &#xa0;\nE\nXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPROPOSED REFORMS\n&#xa0;\nThey are certainly needed but I d\noubt whether they are sufficient to make all the improvements\n that could be achieved given the right emphasis and direction\n. They are a good stepping stone but are not the complete answer. \n&#xa0;\nThese proposed reforms will only be effective to a limited extent. They will highlight the problem and identify the areas of failure and point out the providers and local authorities who are falling below acceptable minimum standards. What is \nmissing is the cure to the problems of children being place in underperforming homes in remote locations.\nMAYFIELD CHILDREN’S HOME\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPLACING CHILDREN INTO RESIDENTIAL CARE\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nTHE CORPORATE MODEL OF \nCHILDREN’S HOMES\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFUNDAMENTAL PROBLEMS IN THE RESIDENTIAL SECTOR\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nTRANSPARENCY\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHIGHER QUALITY\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nTOUGHER INSPECTIONS\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"